marvel /ˈmɑːvəl/

(marvelling,marvelled,marvels) AM marveling , marveled 

1. V-I If you marvel at something, you express your great surprise, wonder, or admiration. 大为赞叹 

例： Her fellow members marvelled at her seemingly infinite energy. 她的同事们对她那似乎无尽的精力大为赞叹。 

例： Sara and I read the story and marvelled. 我和萨拉读了这个故事后惊叹不已。 

2. N-COUNT You can describe something or someone as a marvel to indicate that you think that they are wonderful. 奇迹 

例： The whale, like the dolphin, has become a symbol of the marvels of creation. 鲸，和海豚一样，已经成为造物杰作的象征。

</div>

